\title{Section of Type Family}
\taxon{Definition}
\p{
    Let #{B} be a [type family](def-0018) over #{A} in context #{\Gamma}.
    A \strong{section} of #{B} is a term #{b} of type #{B(x)} in context #{\Gamma,x:A}.
    ##{
        \Gamma, x:A \vdash b : B(x)
    }
    Alternatively, we say that #{b} is a term of #{B(x)} indexed by #{x:A} in context #{\Gamma}.
}